<TITLE> Stocks end down as investors offload </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 17 (bdnews24.com)The country's bourses ended down Sunday as retail investors offloaded shares to lock in profits. State-run oil companies, the power sector, banks and mutual funds paced the day's trading. Banks ended mixed, while power and oil issues closed downbeat. The market, however, saw a rise in mutual funds. Market analysts said investors had been cautious throughout the day, which had led to fluctuations in the share prices of issues. "One day investors favour a certain scrip, which causes the price to rise, the next day they are selling it off to gain their profit," said a top official of a broker house. "The market has been very unpredictable for the last few days," he added. The Dhaka Stock Exchange's general index rose slightly at the opening bell, dipping in midday trade, before recovering its losses towards close. The benchmark DGEN or general index closed at 2936.06, down 33.63 points, or 1.13 percent. The DSI or all share price index ended on 2478.81, down 23.03 points, or 0.92 percent. The blue chip DSE-20 closed on 2319.27, falling 23.77 points, or 1.01 percent. Turnover on the country's prime bourse stood at Tk 2.15 billion, from 13,769,951 traded shares. Losers beat gainers 147 to 73, with thirteen scrips holding steady. Jamuna Oil topped the turnover board, falling 0.93 percent to end on Tk 326.70. Meghna Petroleum followed, ending on Tk 325.10, down 0.73 percent. AB Bank slipped 1.77 percent to end on Tk 2830. Summit Power, which traded on the spot market, fell 0.67 percent to end on Tk 1589.25. Grameen Mutual Fund One gained 2.32 percent to end on Tk 118.60. Among other scrips on the turnover board: Beximco Pharma, BRAC Bank and IFIC Bank declined; AIMS 1st Mutual Fund and UCBL gained. All indices on the Chittagong Stock Exchange also ended lower. The CSCX or selective categories index ended on 4788.92, down 48.51 points, or 1.00 percent. The CASPI or all share price index closed at 7484.30, shedding 56.37 points, or 0.74 percent. The blue chip CSE-30 index ended on 6678.07, down 60.23 points, or 0.89 percent. Turnover totalled Tk 296.67 million from 2,542,029 traded shares. Of the issues traded 31 advanced, 95 declined and six remained unchanged. bdn
